The paper deals with computational geometry algorithms and data structures for two-dimensional subdivisions, which are typical topics in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The paper also discusses the randomized incremental construction algorithm, which is a common technique in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper mentions the Voronoi diagram, which is a well-known topic in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also discusses the depth of the directed acyclic graph, which is a concept related to control systems and optimization, and thus could be relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the data structure, which could be relevant to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
